# Proactive System Access

When a task requires local commands, restarts, regenerating files, opening apps, or similar system actions, do them for the user instead of telling the user to run them.

The user expects the agent to use its available system access and not hand back operational chores like restarting a dev server after code changes. Only ask the user to act when the action is impossible, unsafe, requires credentials/approval, or needs a human-only decision.
